Bloomberg News and The Washington
Post will sponsor a debate of the candidates for the  Republican
Party ’s 2012 presidential nomination focused on economic issues
tonight at Dartmouth College in Hanover, New Hampshire.  The debate featuring eight Republican candidates will be
moderated by  Charlie Rose  starting at 8 p.m. EDT.  On the web, see a live-stream of the discussion at
 http://www.bloomberg.com .  It will be broadcast on Bloomberg Television,
Bloomberg Radio and WBIN-TV. For a listing for Bloomberg TV on 
cable stations, see  http://www.bloomberg.com/tv/channel-finder .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Silva in Washington at 
